HEADWORD: Maypole
<hw>May"pole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tall pole erected
in an open place and wreathed with flowers, about which the rustic
May-day sports were had.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

